---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import StatGrid from '../../components/StatGrid.astro';

const metrics = [
  { label: 'Platform fee', value: '$0', note: 'was $400/yr' },
  { label: 'Mobile speed', value: '76 → 98', note: 'Google score' },
  { label: 'Page weight', value: '1.7 MB → 193 KB', note: 'mobile home' },
  { label: 'Largest paint', value: '6.5 s → 1.8 s', note: 'mobile LCP' },
];
---

<Base
  title="Case study: Rusty the Raccoon — Gian Trotta"
  description="How a children's book author escaped a $400/yr Wix bill, cut page weight from 1.7 MB to 193 KB, and got a site Google can actually read."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 pb-12 pt-16">
    <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-accent">Website Rescue · Case study</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
      Rusty the Raccoon
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-lg text-mist">
      A children's book author was paying $400 a year for a site Google thought was called
      "My Site." I rebuilt it in a day: same content, zero platform fee, and pages that load
      before you finish blinking.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-6">
      <a
        href="https://www.rustytheraccoon.com/"
        class="font-semibold text-steel underline"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noreferrer noopener"
      >
        See the live site →
      </a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Proof strip -->
  <section class="border-y border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-10">
      <p class="eyebrow">At a glance · before → after</p>
      <div class="mt-6">
        <StatGrid stats={metrics} cols={4} noteClass="mt-1 font-utility text-xs" />
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-sm text-mist">
        Before measured 2026-07-17 against the still-live Wix copy at michelletrotta20.wixsite.com/my-site.
        After measured the same day on rustytheraccoon.com.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-accent">The problem</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Paying rent on a site Google ignored</h2>
    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-mist">
      <p>
        Michelle Trotta wrote and published <em>Rusty the Raccoon is Scared of the Dark</em>, a
        picture book for kids who are nervous about the dark. Her site had seven pages: book info,
        author bio, free activity downloads, resource links, and videos. Nothing fancy. Just what
        a small publisher needs.
      </p>
      <p>
        It was on Wix, and the annual bill was <strong class="text-ink">$400</strong>. The renewal
        was due August 3, 2026. If she cancelled the plan, the whole site would disappear August 22.
      </p>
      <p>
        On a phone, the old home page weighed about <strong class="text-ink">1.7 MB</strong> and took
        <strong class="text-ink">6.5 seconds</strong> before the main content finished painting. Search
        was worse. Every page title said <strong class="text-ink">"My Site."</strong> Not the book
        name. Not the author. "My Site," on every single page.
      </p>
      <p>
        Michelle wanted to keep her content — the same words, the same downloads, the same look and
        feel. She wanted to stop paying platform rent for a site that wasn't pulling its weight.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What we did -->
  <section class="border-t border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-accent">What we did</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Rescue the content, then rebuild</h2>
      <div class="mt-8 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">1. Archive everything first</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            Before touching the builder or the DNS, I downloaded every page, all 24 images, and
            all 11 activity PDFs. Once the content was safe on disk, the Wix deadline had a lot
            less leverage.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">2. Rebuild by hand</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            I rebuilt all seven pages as a lightweight static site — no monthly platform, no bloated
            page builder. Same copy, cleaner URLs, and real page titles that say what's on the page.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">3. Make Google understand the book</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            Every page got its own title and description. I added a sitemap, plus structured data so
            search engines know this is a book by a real author with an Amazon link. Google Search
            Console registered and the sitemap submitted — on launch day.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="border border-line bg-porcelain p-6">
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">4. Keep the old links working</h3>
          <p class="mt-3 text-mist">
            Old Wix URLs from bookmarks and search results were redirected. Activity PDFs people had
            linked to on the old file server still download. Michelle reviewed the preview and signed
            off before I touched the domain.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Results -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-accent">Results</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">The numbers</h2>

    <div class="mt-10 grid items-start gap-10 lg:grid-cols-12">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7">
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">$400/year → $0 hosting</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              The Wix site plan was cancelled before the August renewal. Hosting is free. The only
              recurring cost left is domain registration through Wix until the contract ends in 2027.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">"My Site" → real page titles</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              The home page now opens with <em>Rusty the Raccoon is Scared of the Dark</em>, the
              actual book name. Every page has its own title and description. Basic stuff, but the
              old site never had it.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">1.7 MB → 193 KB · 6.5 s → 1.8 s</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              On a phone, the home page dropped from about 1.7 MB to 193 KB. The main content used to
              take 6.5 seconds to finish painting; now it takes 1.8 seconds, with a Google speed score
              of 98, up from 76. Desktop is 100/100, with main content in 0.3 seconds. The server
              answers in about 30 milliseconds instead of over a second.
            </p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold">Registered with Google</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-mist">
              Search Console verified on launch day. Sitemap submitted. The site is ready to be
              crawled and indexed, which the old Wix site never was.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>

        <blockquote class="mt-10 border-l-4 border-flare pl-6">
          <p class="text-lg italic text-ink">
            Michelle reviewed the preview before we flipped the domain. Her verdict: she loves it.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>

      <!-- Receipt-style scoreboard -->
      <aside
        class="receipt-wrap lg:col-span-5 lg:rotate-1 motion-reduce:rotate-0"
        aria-label="Before and after measured results"
      >
        <div class="receipt-paper px-7 py-9 font-utility">
          <p class="eyebrow">Site checkup · before → after</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-xs text-mist">Measured 2026-07-17 · mobile</p>
          <dl class="mt-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Speed score</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">76</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">98</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Largest paint</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">6.5 s</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">1.8 s</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Page weight</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">1.7 MB</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">193 KB</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Server response</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">1.1 s</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">30 ms</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4 border-b border-dotted border-line pb-3">
              <dt>Page titles</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">"My Site"</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-steel">unique</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between gap-4">
              <dt>Platform fee</dt>
              <dd class="text-right font-bold">
                <span class="text-mist line-through">$400/yr</span>
                <span aria-hidden="true" class="mx-1 text-mist">→</span>
                <span class="text-flare-deep">$0</span>
              </dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
          <p class="mt-6 border-t border-dashed border-line pt-4 text-xs leading-relaxed text-mist">
            Before: michelletrotta20.wixsite.com/my-site. After: rustytheraccoon.com. Desktop after
            also hits 100/100 speed with a 0.3 s largest paint.
          </p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Timeline note -->
  <section class="border-t border-line bg-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-12">
      <p class="eyebrow">Timeline</p>
      <p class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-mist">
        The whole project happened in one day: July 12, 2026. Scrape, rebuild, design review, search
        setup, DNS cutover, and Wix cancellation. Michelle had a preview to approve before anything
        went live on her domain. The free Wix subdomain copy was still online on July 17, which is
        how I captured the before scores after the fact.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16">
    <div class="border-2 border-dashed border-ink bg-white p-8 sm:p-10">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow-accent">Sound familiar?</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-display text-2xl font-bold sm:text-3xl">
        Paying monthly for a slow site Google barely knows exists?
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl text-mist">
        Start with a free 15-minute call or a fixed-price Site Checkup. You'll leave knowing what
        your site needs, whether or not we work together.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn-primary">
          Book a free call
        </a>
        <a href="/services/" class="btn-secondary">
          See services
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
